vi <file1>   open <file1>, create a new if it does not exist

press 'i' key to enter 'insert'/writing mode and beging typing

Once done writing, press 'Esc' key to leave 'insert'/writing mode

save and exit by typing :x 

dd           delete the current line 
5dd          delete 5 lines

yy           copy the current line 
5yy          copy 5 lines

p            paste the copied line(s)

To discard any changes to the file while exiting,

type :q!

Ctrl+D        page down
Ctrl+U        page up

